    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:help pumborder` states that it works like `winborder` and it says `The default value is empty, which is equivalent to \"none\"`.\n\nHowever, when popup menu is triggered by <Tab> in commandline, it shows up in different position.\n\n<img width=\"387\" height=\"292\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/905735bd-6bf4-4f60-bb4c-65266f3d8ad2\" />\n\n<img width=\"387\" height=\"292\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/62327b3d-77ae-4334-8c41-581d2196f6a4\" />\n\nI found out that popup window's border width is decided by `*p_pumborder != NUL` check(which does not check \"none\" case), and it seems like the patch below works. \n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/popupmenu.c b/src/nvim/popupmenu.c\nindex e172c6f312..2e1d8a1791 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/popupmenu.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/popupmenu.c\n@@ -297,9 +297,10 @@ void pum_display(pumitem_T *array, int size, int selected, bool array_changed, i\n \n   pum_rl = (State & MODE_CMDLINE) == 0 && curwin->w_p_rl;\n \n-  int pum_border_size = *p_pumborder != NUL ? 2 : 0;\n+  int pum_border_size = *p_pumborder != NUL && !strequal(p_pumborder,\n+                                                         opt_winborder_values[7]) ? 2 : 0;\n   if (strequal(p_pumborder, opt_winborder_values[3])) {\n     pum_border_size -= 1;\n   }\n \n   do {\n@@ -604,7 +605,7 @@ void pum_redraw(void)\n   WinConfig fconfig = WIN_CONFIG_INIT;\n   int pum_border_width = 0;\n   // setup popup menu border if 'pumborder' option is set\n-  if (*p_pumborder != NUL) {\n+  if (*p_pumborder != NUL && !strequal(p_pumborder, opt_winborder_values[7])) {\n     pum_border_width = 2;\n     fconfig.border = true;\n     Error err = ERROR_INIT;\n\n```\n\nHowever, since I don't fully understand the whole related code, I'm not sure that it's sufficient fix. `pum_adjust_info_position` function also uses `*p_pumborder != NUL` check, but I didn't dig deeper when it's used. Should it also be changed?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. trigger pum by `:set pumborder=<Tab>`\n3. set `pumborder` to `none`. `:set pumborder=none`\n4. trigger pum again. `:set pumborder=<Tab>`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\npumborder=none should show default behavior.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1459+g0791594101\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal 3.52.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
